Sample applications for using with cloudark (https://github.com/cloud-ark/cloudark.git)

Comments
---------

1) SSH into ECS cluster instance

- Find out location of the .pem file for your cluster

  - cld environment show <env-id>

- cd into the directory where the .pem file is located

- Change permissions

  - chmod 400 <pem file>

- Find out IP of the cluster instance from AWS web console

- SSH into the cluster instance

  - ssh -i "<pem file>" ec2-user@<AWS cluster instance IP>


2) If you run into any issues, please file an issue (https://github.com/cloud-ark/cloudark/issues)

   - Include your environment yaml file
   - Include relevant log information from cld.log (this file is created in the cloudark directory)